'''樟宜机场地铁站'''（{{lang-en|Changi Airport MRT Station}}，編號：{{lang|en|CG2}}）是[[新加坡地铁|新加坡地铁]][[东西线_(新加坡地铁)|东西线]]樟宜机场支线的地铁站，位于[[樟宜机场|樟宜机场]]内。该站由[[SMRT集团|SMRT集团]]运营，呈东西向，两端直接连接樟宜机场2号和3号航站楼。樟宜机场地铁站是樟宜机场支线的东端终点站，也是現時新加坡最东边的地铁站。

1994年，樟宜机场3号航站楼建设期间，有人建议建造一条新的地铁线路连接机场及其周围。1996年，樟宜机场支线的興建計劃獲敲定，随后于1999年开始动工，并与2002年2月8日啓用。尽管乘客数低于预期，该站仍提供了一个通往机场的替代交通选择。2019年5月25日，新加坡[[陆路交通管理局|陆路交通管理局]]宣布，2040年之前[[新加坡地铁汤申－东海岸线|汤申－东海岸线]]将连接樟宜机场5号航站楼，届时樟宜机场站将成为汤申－东海岸线上的一个站。<ref name="LTMP 2040">{{Cite web|url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/new-mrt-stations-tel-extension-and-possible-new-rail-line-lta-2040-blueprint|title=New MRT stations, line extensions and a possible new rail line: LTA's 2040 blueprint|website=TODAYonline|access-date=2019-05-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190525081451/https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/new-mrt-stations-tel-extension-and-possible-new-rail-line-lta-2040-blueprint|archive-date=2019-05-25|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="LTA Masterplan 2040">{{Cite web|url=https://www.lta.gov.sg/apps/news/page.aspx?c=2&id=de83f659-4b0d-4609-840e-3deb3ac9b4b9|title=Land Transport Master Plan 2040: Bringing Singapore Together {{!}} Press Room {{!}} Land Transport Authority|website=www.lta.gov.sg|access-date=2019-05-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823063103/https://www.lta.gov.sg/apps/news/page.aspx?c=2&id=de83f659-4b0d-4609-840e-3deb3ac9b4b9|archive-date=2019-08-23|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==歷史==
[[File:CG2_Changi_Airport_MRT_platforms_20200919_212555.jpg|left]]
樟宜机场于1981年啓用，起初没有[[機場聯絡軌道系統|聯外鐵路]]，只有{{link-en|新加坡德士服務|Taxis of Singapore|德士}}和[[新加坡巴士服务|巴士]]服务。连接机场和市区的[[东海岸公园大道|东海岸公园大道]]很短，只有20公里，而且德士和巴士的車費也很便宜，此外还有巴士來往樟宜機場附近的[[勿洛站|勿洛站]]、[[淡滨尼站|淡滨尼站]]和[[巴西立站|巴西立站]]，因此政府認為機場的聯外交通已能應付當時的需求，不接纳将地铁延伸到机场的建议。<ref>{{Cite news|title=MRT Link to Airport: Not in next 10 years|date=1991-05-17|work=The Straits Times}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=No MRT Line to Changi yet|date=1992-03-20|work=The Straits Times}}</ref>

將地鐵延伸至機場的提議在建造3號客運大樓時獲重提<ref>{{Cite news|title=MRT extension to airport reconsidered.|date=1994-08-02|work=The Straits Times}}</ref>。早期規劃為從現有的東西線上的[[丹那美拉地鐵站|丹那美拉地鐵站]]分出一條支線<ref>{{Cite news|title=Next Stop: Changi Airport?|date=1994-08-02|work=The New Paper}}</ref>，並概念性地規劃沿机场林荫道（{{lang|en|Airport Boulevard}}）通往樟宜機場，然後繼續穿過機場抵達{{link-en|樟宜村|Changi Village|樟宜尾}}，再沿東海岸轉向西南方返回市中心的暫定路線。最終計劃由時任{{tsl|en|Deputy Prime Minister of Singapore|新加坡副總理}}[[李显龙|李显龙]]在1996年11月15日正式公佈<ref>{{cite web |title=Singapore Mass Rapid Transit Employees' Union (SMRTEU)'s annual Dinner and Dance |url=http://www.nas.gov.sg/archivesonline/data/pdfdoc/1996111503/lhl19961115s.pdf |website=NAS |accessdate=2019-07-10 |date=1996-11-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190710173937/http://www.nas.gov.sg/archivesonline/data/pdfdoc/1996111503/lhl19961115s.pdf |archive-date=2019-07-10 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，惟與早期規劃不同，最終定線僅興建原有支線的最初兩站，即[[博覽地鐵站|博覽地鐵站]]與位於2号和3号搭客大厦之間的地底的樟宜机场地铁站。樟宜机场地铁站的位置亦被調整為東西向，使地铁站的兩端均可分別通往兩座客運大樓<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Article/straitstimes19961212-1.2.51.7 |title=MRT Line will not go beyond passenger terminals |website=The Straits Times |access-date=2019-10-17 |date=1996-12-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191017004323/http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Article/straitstimes19961212-1.2.51.7 |archive-date=2019-10-17 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Search|title=Changi Airport MRT line details|date=1996-12-12|work=The Business Times|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171026174816/http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Search|archive-date=2017-10-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>。作為2001年{{link-en|总统挑战|President's Challenge}}的一部分，當年的慈善步行的路線亦經過博覽地鐵站和樟宜機場地鐵站之間的隧道<ref>{{Cite news|last=Seng Kim|first=Lim|url=https://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Search|title=Charity walk to talk place underground|date=2001-08-12|work=The Straits Times|access-date=|dead-url=no|archive-date=2019-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191117154540/http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Search}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|title=Perfectly legal, and for a good cause!|date=2001-09-09|work=The New Paper|access-date=|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Tan|first=Terence|title=Tunnel walk a hit|date=2001-09-09|work=The Straits Times|access-date=|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===建造工程===
[[File:Changi_Airport_MRT_Station-wicket-20121111.jpg|left]]同层的新加坡地铁站]]
1998年10月，[[熊谷組|熊谷組]]-三巴旺工程建設（{{lang|en|Sembawang Engineering and Construction}}）聯營投得價值2.045億[[新加坡元|新加坡元]]的504號合約，以建造樟宜機場地鐵站及其相關隧道、2號和3號客運大樓之間的新行李隧道，以及服務3號客運大樓的行車下通道<ref>{{cite news |title=Joint Venture of SembCorp unit wins MRT contract |work=The Business Times |date=1998-11-03|page=16}}</ref>。由於樟宜機場地鐵站的建造工程上出現挑戰，來自日本的技術、經驗與新加坡當地有關外判商、供應商的可用性的知識的相互結合成為該工程項目的一大需求<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://library.jsce.or.jp/jsce/open/00035/2001/56-cs/56-cs-0266.pdf|title=Underpinning Works in Construction of MRT Changi Airport Station in Singapore|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030025639/http://library.jsce.or.jp/jsce/open/00035/2001/56-cs/56-cs-0266.pdf|archive-date=2020-10-30|access-date=2020-09-30}}</ref>。

奠基典禮於1999年1月29日進行。時任[[新加坡国家发展部|新加坡国家发展部]]部長[[马宝山|马宝山]]在奠基典禮中致辭時強調了樟宜機場地鐵站的建造工程的挑戰，以及[[陆路交通管理局|陆路交通管理局]]、[[新加坡民航局|新加坡民航局]]與承建商等各方之間密切合作的必要性。樟宜機場地鐵站的興建過程中透過使用各種地面支撐系統進行了不同的深挖方法。樟宜機場地鐵站的建造工程的挑戰包括直接在鄰近的開發項目（例如現有的2號客運大樓）旁進行深挖工程<ref name="Excavations">{{Cite book|last=Murugamoorthy|first=C.|title=Behaviour of Various Support Systems for Deep Excavations, Changi Airport Underground MRT Station|publisher=Land Transport Authority|year=2003|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>。此外，直穿機場跑道與客運大樓、通往樟宜機場地鐵站的{{convert|1|km|mi}}長隧道的興建過程亦需要密切監測<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nas.gov.sg/archivesonline/data/pdfdoc/1999012901.htm|title=Speech By Mr Mah Bow Tan, At The Changi Airport Line Ground Breaking Ceremony, 29 Jan 99, 10 am, Singapore Changi Airport|website=www.nas.gov.sg|access-date=2020-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191229100549/https://www.nas.gov.sg/archivesonline/data/pdfdoc/1999012901.htm|archive-date=2019-12-29|dead-url=no}}</ref>。設計3號客運大樓的{{link-en|新加坡CPG集团私人有限公司|CPG Corporation|CPG顧問}}在建造工程期間提供了20名職員予陸路交通管理局團隊，以在樟宜機場支線工程上提供協助<ref name="CPG consultants">{{Cite web|url=https://www.cpgcorp.com.sg/cpgc/Project/Project_Details?ProjectID=1312|title=CPG Consultants – Changi Airport Mass Rapid Transit Station (MRT)|website=www.cpgcorp.com.sg|access-date=2020-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180221174601/http://www.cpgcorp.com.sg/CPGC/Project/Project_Details?ProjectID=1312|archive-date=2018-02-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===啓用===
樟宜機場地鐵站於2002年2月8日對外開放<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mot.gov.sg/news-centre/news/Detail/Completion%20Of%20The%20Changi%20Airport%20MRT%20Extension/|title=Completion Of The Changi Airport MRT Extension|website=www.mot.gov.sg|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09|archive-date=2020-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821064823/https://www.mot.gov.sg/news-centre/news/Detail/Completion%20Of%20The%20Changi%20Airport%20MRT%20Extension/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Search?ST=1&AT=advanced&K=Changi%20Airport%20Station&KA=Changi%20Airport%20Station&DF=01%2F04%2F2001&DT=01%2F08%2F2003&Display=0&NPT=&L=&CTA=Article#|title=Airport MRT stop to open tomorrow|date=2002-02-07|work=Today|access-date=|dead-url=no|archive-date=2020-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821064820/https://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Search?ST=1&AT=advanced&K=Changi+Airport+Station&KA=Changi+Airport+Station&DF=01%2F04%2F2001&DT=01%2F08%2F2003&Display=0&NPT=&L=&CTA=Article}}</ref>，並與樟宜機場支線一同於同月27日正式啓用<ref name="Speech 1">{{Cite web|url=http://www.mot.gov.sg/news-centre/news/Detail/Speech%20By%20Mr%20Yeo%20Cheow%20Tong%20At%20The%20Opening%20Of%20The%20Changi%20Airport%20MRT%20Extension%20on%2027%20February%202002/|title=Speech By Mr Yeo Cheow Tong At The Opening Of The Changi Airport MRT Extension on 27 February 2002|website=www.mot.gov.sg|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09|archive-date=2020-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821064817/https://www.mot.gov.sg/news-centre/news/Detail/Speech%20By%20Mr%20Yeo%20Cheow%20Tong%20At%20The%20Opening%20Of%20The%20Changi%20Airport%20MRT%20Extension%20on%2027%20February%202002/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。自樟宜機場地鐵站啓用以來，由於大多數巴士路線仍繼續運作，對樟宜機場與各航空公司的新加坡員工，以及並非居住於東西線沿線的旅客而言，巴士服務仍是較受歡迎、廉價且直接的交通工具，因此樟宜機場地鐵站的客量一直保持中等水平。此外，由於並非所有的地鐵列車均設有行李架，許多乘坐飛機的旅客仍繼續乘坐德士或私人交通工具來往機場<ref>{{Cite news|last=Seng Kim|first=Chew|url=https://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Search?ST=1&AT=advanced&K=Changi%20Airport%20Station&KA=Changi%20Airport%20Station&DF=01%2F04%2F2001&DT=01%2F08%2F2003&Display=0&NPT=&L=&CTA=Article#|title=Taxi still the way to go for Changi air travellers|date=2002-08-26|work=The Straits Times|access-date=|dead-url=no|archive-date=2020-08-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200821064820/https://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Search?ST=1&AT=advanced&K=Changi+Airport+Station&KA=Changi+Airport+Station&DF=01%2F04%2F2001&DT=01%2F08%2F2003&Display=0&NPT=&L=&CTA=Article}}</ref>。然而，德士司機則稱樟宜機場地鐵站使他們的收入下降了20%，而截至2002年3月，每天約有{{nts|20500}}名通勤者使用樟宜機場地鐵站<ref>{{Cite news|last=Phei Phei|first=Leong|url=https://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Article/today20020311-2.2.4.11?ST=1&AT=advanced&K=Changi%20Airport%20Station&KA=Changi%20Airport%20Station&DF=01%2F04%2F2001&DT=01%2F08%2F2003&Display=0&NPT=&L=&CTA=Article&QT=changi,airport,station&oref=article|title=Airport woes for cabbies|date=2002-03-11|work=Today|access-date=|dead-url=no|archive-date=2020-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030025643/https://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Article/today20020311-2.2.4.11?ST=1&AT=advanced&K=Changi+Airport+Station&KA=Changi+Airport+Station&DF=01%2F04%2F2001&DT=01%2F08%2F2003&Display=0&NPT=&L=&CTA=Article&QT=changi%2Cairport%2Cstation&oref=article}}</ref>。

===劃入湯申－東海岸線===
2016年7月，時任[[新加坡交通部|新加坡交通部]]部長[[许文远|许文远]]宣佈政府正考慮將[[汤申－东海岸线|汤申－东海岸线]]延長到樟宜機場5號客運大樓，以提供更直接來往樟宜機場與市中心的交通連接<ref name="Lim 2016">{{cite web | last=Lim | first=Adrian | title=Thomson-East Coast MRT line may be extended to airport | website=The Straits Times | date=2016-07-22 | url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/thomson-east-coast-mrt-line-may-be-extended-to-airport | access-date=2021-03-25 | archive-date=2021-03-25 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210325130422/https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/transport/thomson-east-coast-mrt-line-may-be-extended-to-airport | dead-url=no }}</ref>。2019年5月25日，陸路交通管理局宣佈在汤申－东海岸线自[[雙溪勿洛地鐵站|雙溪勿洛地鐵站]]延長到樟宜機場5號客運大樓後，樟宜機場支線將劃入湯申－東海岸線<ref name="LTMP 2040"/><ref name="Chong 2019">{{cite web | last=Chong | first=Aaron | title=New stations, line extensions planned for Singapore’s rail network | website=CNA | date=2019-05-25 | url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/new-mrt-stations-lines-lta-master-plan-11564622 | access-date=2021-03-25 | archive-date=2020-02-13 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200213091440/https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/new-mrt-stations-lines-lta-master-plan-11564622 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

===事故===
2002年7月24日，樟宜機場地鐵站中庭的玻璃幕牆碎裂。中庭一帶迅速封閉，惟地鐵列車服務不受影響<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mot.gov.sg/News-Centre/News/2002/Joint-Press-Release-By-Land-Transport-Authority-And-Singapore-MRT-Ltd-Atria-Wall-In-Changi-Airport-MRT-Station/ |title=Joint Press Release By Land Transport Authority And Singapore MRT Ltd Atria Wall In Changi Airport MRT Station |author=<!--Not stated--> |date=2002-07-24 |publisher=[[新加坡交通部|Ministry of Transport]] |access-date=2018-01-16 |quote=At 12.05pm, a piece of tempered glass at the atria wall in the Changi Airport MRT Station shattered into small fragments. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180116135244/https://www.mot.gov.sg/News-Centre/News/2002/Joint-Press-Release-By-Land-Transport-Authority-And-Singapore-MRT-Ltd-Atria-Wall-In-Changi-Airport-MRT-Station/ |archive-date=2018-01-16 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mot.gov.sg/news-centre/news/Detail/Joint%20Press%20Release%20By%20Land%20Transport%20Authority%20And%20Singapore%20MRT%20Ltd%20Atria%20Wall%20In%20Changi%20Airport%20MRT%20Station/|title=Joint Press Release By Land Transport Authority And Singapore MRT Ltd Atria Wall In Changi Airport MRT Station|website=www.mot.gov.sg|language=en|access-date=2020-04-09|archive-date=2020-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030025643/https://www.mot.gov.sg/news-centre/news/Detail/Joint%20Press%20Release%20By%20Land%20Transport%20Authority%20And%20Singapore%20MRT%20Ltd%20Atria%20Wall%20In%20Changi%20Airport%20MRT%20Station/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2003年9月24日，一名男子因樟宜機場地鐵站在自離境大堂墮下五層樓而死<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Article/today20030925-2.2.11.1|title=Man Dies at Changi Airport|date=2003-09-25|work=TODAY|access-date=2017-10-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171218042611/http://eresources.nlb.gov.sg/newspapers/Digitised/Article/today20030925-2.2.11.1|archive-date=2017-12-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2020年1月17日，SMRT集團稱其於晨早檢查工作中在樟宜機場地鐵站的路軌交叉處發現裂縫。地鐵列車須改道至同一月台上落客，並且在接近受影響的路軌交叉處時須以較慢的速度行駛<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/slower-train-service-changi-airport-mrt-station-until-jan-21-after-crack-spotted-track|title=Slower train service to Changi Airport MRT Station until Jan 21, after crack spotted on track|date=2020-01-17|work=Today|access-date=|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200118145036/https://www.todayonline.com/singapore/slower-train-service-changi-airport-mrt-station-until-jan-21-after-crack-spotted-track|archive-date=2020-01-18}}</ref>。

